### Create a new working project

```bash
# Create a new working project named `attaching-disks-demo`
oc new-project attaching-disks-demo

# Swith the `attaching-disks-demo` project
oc project externalaccess-demo
```

### Create two Web VMs.

Create two VMs named `web1` and `web2` from the `rhel10-helloworld` instance type.

### Attach an SCSI disk to `web1`

Attach a SCSI disk to VM1 and make it persistent. 

Format it and mount it, 

mkfs.ext4 /dev/sda

mount /var/www/html /dev/sda

restorecon -FRv /var/www/html

Put some content on it. Test the Web content is accessible


Check the disk UIID with `lsblk -fp`, then permanently mount the disk in /dev/fstab



Detach the disk from VM1 then attach it to VM2. Make is persistent.
Dont' restart the VMs for now.
In VM1, attach a VirtIO disk by cloning it from the previous disk PVC.
Restart VM1 and check the disk is mounted with the same UIID disk, as it was cloned from previous disk PVC.
Expand disks in both VMs and extend their filesystem.

sudo xfs_growfs /dev/sda
